Baxter, a global healthcare company, is actively involved in providing surgical solutions for pediatric patients with athymia. The company's products and services cater to the surgical needs of healthcare providers, ensuring the safe and effective treatment of infants with congenital athymia. Novartis AG, a Swiss multinational pharmaceutical company, is at the forefront of developing cutting-edge therapies for rare diseases like pediatric congenital athymia. The company's focus on precision medicine and personalized treatments holds great promise for improving outcomes in this patient population.

